# Comprehensive .NET/C# Plugin Research for CodeLens

**Date:** 2026-03-17  
**Scope:** Deep research on building a comprehensive .NET plugin suite for CodeLens, covering ASP.NET Core, Entity Framework Core, SignalR, gRPC, MediatR, and middleware analysis.  
**Sources:** CodeLens codebase (plugin architecture, existing Java/Python plugins, Neo4j schema), Microsoft Learn docs, tree-sitter-c-sharp grammar, SCIP-dotnet indexer, ASP.NET Core 9/10 patterns.

---

## 1. Executive Summary

The .NET ecosystem requires **6 plugins** (up from the original 4 in the spec) for comprehensive coverage. The architecture maps directly onto the existing `FrameworkPlugin` ABC — same lifecycle, same Neo4j output types, same detection/ordering/execution pattern. The key difference from Java/Spring is that .NET has **two API paradigms** (controllers + minimal APIs), **three entity configuration paths** (conventions, annotations, Fluent API), and **explicit DI registration** (no classpath scanning). The `tree-sitter-c-sharp` grammar (v0.23.1, C# 1-13 support) and `scip-dotnet` (Roslyn-based SCIP indexer) are both production-ready.

### Recommended Plugin Suite

