## 7. Plugin #5: SignalR Plugin (`aspnet-signalr`)

### 7.1 What It Extracts

Real-time communication hubs, their endpoint mappings, and client-callable methods.

### 7.2 Patterns to Capture

```csharp
// Hub definition
public class ChatHub : Hub
{
    public async Task SendMessage(string user, string message)
    {
        await Clients.All.SendAsync("ReceiveMessage", user, message);
    }

    public async Task JoinGroup(string groupName)
    {
        await Groups.AddToGroupAsync(Context.ConnectionId, groupName);
    }

    public override async Task OnConnectedAsync() { ... }
    public override async Task OnDisconnectedAsync(Exception? exception) { ... }
}

// Strongly-typed hub
public class NotificationHub : Hub<INotificationClient>
{
    public async Task SendNotification(string message)
    {
        await Clients.All.ReceiveNotification(message);
    }
}

public interface INotificationClient
{
    Task ReceiveNotification(string message);
}

// Registration in Program.cs
builder.Services.AddSignalR();
app.MapHub<ChatHub>("/chatHub");
app.MapHub<NotificationHub>("/notifications");
```

### 7.3 Extraction Strategy

1. Find classes inheriting `Hub` or `Hub<T>` (check `base_list`)
2. Extract all public methods (excluding `OnConnectedAsync`, `OnDisconnectedAsync`) as hub methods
3. For `Hub<T>`, extract the interface type `T` and its methods as client-callable methods
4. Find `MapHub<T>("/path")` calls in `Program.cs` to get the endpoint path
5. Find `Clients.All.SendAsync("MethodName", ...)` calls to discover server-to-client events

### 7.4 Output

- **Nodes:** `(:APIEndpoint {method: "WS", path: "/chatHub", framework: "signalr", protocol: "websocket"})`
- **Edges:** `(:Class)-[:EXPOSES]->(:APIEndpoint)`, `(:Method)-[:HANDLES]->(:APIEndpoint)`, `(:Class)-[:PRODUCES {event: "ReceiveMessage"}]->(:APIEndpoint)`
- **Layer assignments:** Hub classes → Presentation layer

### 7.5 Estimated Accuracy: **~90%**

Hub patterns are very explicit — class inheritance, attribute detection, and `MapHub` registration are all unambiguous.

