## 11. What's New / Different for .NET

| Challenge | Impact | Mitigation |
|-----------|--------|------------|
| **Two API paradigms** (controllers + minimal APIs) | Web plugin needs dual extraction paths | Implement both, prefer controller detection first |
| **Fluent API chaining** in EF Core | Harder to parse than Hibernate annotations | Walk `invocation_expression` chains, extract method names as semantic operators |
| **Top-level statements** in `Program.cs` | No class/method wrapper for minimal APIs + middleware | Handle `global_statement` AST nodes |
| **Generic type arguments** for DI | `AddScoped<IFoo, Foo>()` — need reliable generic extraction | Tree-sitter `type_argument_list` → `generic_name` parsing |
| **Convention-based FK resolution** | Requires inference, not explicit declarations | Implement naming convention matcher (`{NavProp}Id` pattern) |
| **`IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>`** pattern | Fluent config in separate files | Detect implementing classes, parse `Configure` method |
| **Lambda expressions** in Fluent API | `u => u.Department` — need to resolve property name | Extract rightmost identifier from `member_access_expression` |
| **File-scoped namespaces** | `namespace Foo;` instead of `namespace Foo { }` | Tree-sitter handles via `file_scoped_namespace_declaration` |

